dcterms:description: The protein dataset is a benchmark for graph generation, containing graphs with 8 nodes where the node features are their 3D coordinate vectors. There are no edge features, and the dataset consists of 76,000 graphs, split evenly for training and testing.
dcterms:title: Protein dataset

dcterms:description: QM9 is a dataset containing quantum chemistry structures and properties of 134,000 molecules, each consisting of up to 9 heavy atoms. The dataset is used for various tasks in molecular generation and property prediction.
dcterms:title: QM9

dcterms:description: ZINC is a dataset for ligand discovery, containing approximately 250,000 molecules, each consisting of 9 to 38 heavy atoms. The dataset is widely used in drug discovery and molecular generation tasks.
dcterms:title: ZINC
